<h2 style="margin:0 0 16px;font-size:20px;font-weight:600;color:#111;line-height:1.3;">
  Command Center disk usage is critical
</h2>

<p style="margin:0 0 20px;font-size:15px;line-height:1.6;color:#374151;">
  {{ notification.body | e }}
</p>

<p style="margin:0 0 20px;padding:14px;background:#fee2e2;border-left:3px solid #ef4444;font-size:14px;color:#7f1d1d;line-height:1.5;">
  This affects <strong>every organization</strong> on this Command Center,
  not just yours. When the disk fills, SQLite writes start failing —
  recordings, audit logs, and motion events stop persisting silently.
  Live HLS streams keep working (they're in-memory) but everything that
  touches the database breaks.
</p>

<p style="margin:0 0 8px;font-size:14px;color:#6b7280;font-weight:600;">
  What to do RIGHT NOW
</p>
<ol style="margin:0 0 24px;padding-left:20px;font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;color:#374151;">
  <li>Open the admin health page (link below) and check disk + log volume.</li>
  <li>Resize the Fly volume (<code style="background:#f3f4f6;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:3px;font-family:ui-monospace,Menlo,monospace;font-size:13px;">fly volumes extend ...</code>) <em>or</em> trigger early log retention cleanup.</li>
  <li>Don't wait for the next email — each follow-up is gated for 6 hours.</li>
</ol>

<table role="presentation" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
  <tr>
    <td style="background:#ef4444;border-radius:6px;">
      <a href="{{ dashboard_url }}/admin/health"
         style="display:inline-block;padding:10px 18px;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#fff;text-decoration:none;">
        Open admin health page →
      </a>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p style="margin:24px 0 0;font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;line-height:1.5;">
  This alert went only to organization admins.
</p>
